        {
            'question': 'What is the most common anesthetic technique seen in the operating theater?',
            'answer': 'A General Anesthetic (GA).',
        },
        {
            'question': 'What analogy is used to describe the phases of a General Anesthetic?',
            'answer': 'Flying a plane, where takeoff (induction) and landing (emergence) are the phases of highest action, and the maintenance phase represents a cruising altitude requiring minor adjustments and constant monitoring.',
        },
        {
            'question': 'What clinical actions are performed during the induction phase of a GA?',
            'answer': 'Application of appropriate monitoring.\nAdministration of oxygen via the anesthetic machine circuit.\nDelivery of a variety of intravenous anesthetic drugs.',
        },
